# My active personal projects

<br>

1. [My blog](https://github.com/Guseyn/guseyn.com).

1.  [<img class="project-logo" style="width: 52px; height: 130px;" src="/image/unison-logo.svg?v=e323858f">](https://unisonofficial.com) [Unison](https://unisonofficial.com) is an online tool that helps you generate music notation using written text. It means that you can just describe music and its structure with simple words and the tool will generate an image by that description.

1. [<img class="project-logo" style="width: 218px; height: 48px;" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,">](https://e-html.org) [EHTML (or Extended HTML)](https://e-html.org) can be described as a set of custom elements that you can put on HTML page for different purposes and use cases. The main idea and goal of this library is to provide a convinient way to get rid of all your JavaScript code on the client side.

1. [<img class="project-logo" style="width: 218px; height: 48px;" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,">](https://e-html.org) [Nodes.js](https://github.com/Guseyn/nodes.js) is a Node.js Procedural Backend Framework with Cluster API based on HTTP/2.

1. [<img class="project-logo" style="width: 150px; height: 140px;" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,">](https://guseyn.github.io/nn-math-web/) [Web Page: Mathematics of Neural Network](https://guseyn.github.io/nn-math-web/) is a project that was created out of dissatisfaction with existing online materials on the mathematics of neural networks. It is simply an extremely precise explanation of mathematics for neural networks with consistent indexing and coherent annotations.
